The biggest challenge for NBA rookies is that they are dealing with far taller, longer and stronger men than they have ever faced on a nightly basis. On top of that, they must contend with the sheer overall intelligence of NBA veterans, who pick on rookies because they know they can early on. But rookies learn quickly. The big question is how fast can they begin to limit their mistakes as they stop "playing the game" and start "reading the actions" -- moving the needle toward a positive impact overall, the clear goal of most rookies. To read David Thorpe's full analysis on the rookies, become an Insider. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits Â» Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe David ThorpeNBA Follow Archive NBA Analyst for ESPN.com Executive director of Pro Training Center Started coaching career in 1987